1
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:55,774
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:55,774 --> 00:00:56,608
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:56,608 --> 00:00:57,409
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:57,409 --> 00:00:58,177
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:01:05,117 --> 00:01:07,486
(Mono Group Chairman Choi Young Ho
shares warmth for the Korean New Year.)

6
00:01:07,486 --> 00:01:09,288
(Joins Hope 2025 Sharing Campaign
for sustainable CSR)

7
00:01:09,288 --> 00:01:11,723
(Visited a flophouse district
to volunteer and offer support)

8
00:01:14,226 --> 00:01:15,260
(Mono Group's major overseas projects
moving smoothly)

9
00:01:15,260 --> 00:01:16,195
(Record-breaking performance
expected this year)

10
00:01:17,162 --> 00:01:18,397
(Successful overseas expansion continues)

11
00:01:20,365 --> 00:01:21,633
(The hidden architect behind the veil)

12
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:22,868
(Chairman Choi Young Ho's
suspicious master plan)

13
00:01:22,868 --> 00:01:24,002
(The illusion of delegated management,
Mono Group's dual structure)

14
00:01:27,139 --> 00:01:28,674
(The hidden architect behind the veil)

15
00:01:28,674 --> 00:01:30,242
(Chairman Choi Young Ho's
suspicious master plan)

16
00:01:31,844 --> 00:01:34,746
Choi Young Ho made a fortune
in overseas construction.

17
00:01:35,614 --> 00:01:37,916
Starting with nothing,
he's come this far...

18
00:01:38,317 --> 00:01:40,385
with almost no real enemies,

19
00:01:40,853 --> 00:01:43,155
which proves his business sense
and ability are exceptional.

20
00:01:50,762 --> 00:01:52,564
(Mono Group)

21
00:01:53,332 --> 00:01:55,033
It's the company he founded,

22
00:01:55,467 --> 00:01:58,437
but for the past few years, he's entrusted
management to Vice Chairman Yoo Min Ho,

23
00:01:59,204 --> 00:02:01,840
and is known to retain
only final decision-making authority.

24
00:02:03,108 --> 00:02:04,376
But many still believe...

25
00:02:04,376 --> 00:02:06,778
he continues to direct and decide
everything behind the scenes,

26
00:02:07,779 --> 00:02:09,615
so he's definitely a man
who is not what he appears to be.

27
00:02:09,615 --> 00:02:12,217
(Choi Hee Su's fiancé - Ryu Jun Ho)

28
00:02:18,090 --> 00:02:20,826
It feels like he's deliberately keeping
his domestic activities to a minimum...

29
00:02:21,527 --> 00:02:23,061
in several different ways.

30
00:02:24,496 --> 00:02:26,298
He's so shrouded in secrecy...

31
00:02:26,765 --> 00:02:28,600
and spends most of his time overseas...

32
00:02:29,201 --> 00:02:30,903
that getting close to him is impossible.

33
00:02:34,473 --> 00:02:37,576
I've heard people say
his plane is his office.

34
00:02:41,113 --> 00:02:43,482
(Kim Soo Yeon)

35
00:02:43,749 --> 00:02:44,750
Mom.

36
00:02:46,118 --> 00:02:48,287
Mom, I'm here.

37
00:02:48,287 --> 00:02:50,222
His wife passed away a few years ago.

38
00:02:51,056 --> 00:02:52,391
Since then,

39
00:02:52,391 --> 00:02:54,760
he's been spending far more time overseas.

40
00:02:55,761 --> 00:02:57,596
He has a daughter studying abroad,

41
00:02:58,564 --> 00:03:00,699
and she's probably around your age.

42
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:03,936
Whatever it is,
if it comes out of that girl's mouth,

43
00:03:03,936 --> 00:03:05,671
you can assume anything is possible.

44
00:03:06,572 --> 00:03:08,240
She's his only blood relative,

45
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,875
so apparently, he's very attached to her.

46
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:18,383
This house?

47
00:03:19,751 --> 00:03:20,919
It was listed at five million dollars...

48
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:22,120
Just like you said,

49
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,789
that girl, Choi Hee Su,

50
00:03:24,256 --> 00:03:25,724
got a place in Hanyeon-dong.

51
00:03:26,692 --> 00:03:28,927
You'll need to find out
exactly where it is.

52
00:03:30,095 --> 00:03:31,063
Of course.

53
00:03:32,197 --> 00:03:33,198
She's lived abroad for a long time,

54
00:03:33,198 --> 00:03:34,967
so she likely doesn't know
many people in Korea.

55
00:03:36,201 --> 00:03:38,203
That means she'll spend
a lot of time at home.

56
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:45,077
Choi Hee Su bought a building
worth over five million dollars...

57
00:03:45,077 --> 00:03:46,445
and uses it as a studio,

58
00:03:47,379 --> 00:03:49,915
but the neighbors say
they've barely even seen her face.

59
00:03:51,483 --> 00:03:52,851
She has a closed-off personality,

60
00:03:53,418 --> 00:03:55,120
so getting close to her won't be easy.

61
00:03:56,522 --> 00:03:58,824
It's clear she doesn't
trust people easily.

62
00:03:59,691 --> 00:04:01,260
She acts exactly like him.

63
00:04:01,894 --> 00:04:03,428
Like father, like daughter.

64
00:04:03,795 --> 00:04:06,899
(Atelier)

65
00:04:06,899 --> 00:04:09,735
(Inner Landscapes: The Flow of Emotion
Choi Hee Su Solo Exhibition)

66
00:04:20,846 --> 00:04:22,881
Which piece are you most attached to?

67
00:04:22,881 --> 00:04:26,151
This is my first solo exhibition in Korea,

68
00:04:26,151 --> 00:04:29,988
so I tried to put a bit of my emotions
into each piece.

69
00:04:29,988 --> 00:04:31,490
She majored in painting,

70
00:04:32,291 --> 00:04:34,326
and she's fairly well known
in the industry.

71
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,929
Her skills are top-notch.

72
00:04:38,096 --> 00:04:40,132
She's not some rich girl...

73
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,901
who lives off her family and does nothing.

74
00:04:45,804 --> 00:04:47,840
The only way to meet Choi Young Ho...

75
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:51,276
is to approach this girl
and wait for an opening.

76
00:04:52,878 --> 00:04:55,113
I don't see any other way.

77
00:05:03,555 --> 00:05:05,624
This is where it gets difficult.

78
00:05:06,792 --> 00:05:08,727
Think carefully about how to approach her,

79
00:05:09,595 --> 00:05:11,463
then act with caution.

80
00:05:12,498 --> 00:05:14,366
There must be countless people
swarming around,

81
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:16,969
looking for a way to get something...

82
00:05:16,969 --> 00:05:18,403
out of that rich man.

83
00:05:19,805 --> 00:05:22,574
The moment you look like one of them,
your chance is gone.

84
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:23,742
Forever.

85
00:05:36,622 --> 00:05:38,123
Sorry, but let's finish the interview.

86
00:05:38,123 --> 00:05:39,658
Please take a good look around.

87
00:05:40,325 --> 00:05:41,460
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

88
00:06:19,064 --> 00:06:20,098
Hello.

89
00:06:23,702 --> 00:06:25,337
For a moment, I had this thought.

90
00:06:27,105 --> 00:06:28,207
Maybe my target...

91
00:06:28,207 --> 00:06:30,609
should include the daughter
Choi Young Ho treasures so much,

92
00:06:32,277 --> 00:06:34,079
Choi Hee Su too.

93
00:06:36,882 --> 00:06:39,618
He killed someone else's family
while protecting his own blood,

94
00:06:39,618 --> 00:06:42,354
so maybe that would be
a more fitting way...

95
00:06:43,021 --> 00:06:45,424
to take revenge on that shameless old man.

96
00:06:45,691 --> 00:06:47,326
Do you like the painting?

97
00:06:49,394 --> 00:06:51,163
That's when one idea came to me.

98
00:06:52,297 --> 00:06:53,599
- Thank you.
- Maybe,

99
00:06:55,167 --> 00:06:56,568
Choi Young Ho's end...

100
00:06:58,170 --> 00:07:00,072
will be crueler than I expected.

101
00:07:02,808 --> 00:07:05,344
Because there's no such thing
as revenge that only gives back...

102
00:07:07,312 --> 00:07:08,347
what was done to you.

103
00:07:11,650 --> 00:07:15,020
(Revenge)

104
00:07:27,866 --> 00:07:29,535
Come here, honey.

105
00:07:30,969 --> 00:07:32,671
I'm home.

106
00:07:33,672 --> 00:07:35,707
Why do you look so down?

107
00:07:36,141 --> 00:07:37,209
Did something happen?

108
00:07:37,509 --> 00:07:39,244
- No, nothing.
- Really?

109
00:07:40,812 --> 00:07:41,880
Ms. Ham Myo Jin.

110
00:07:42,447 --> 00:07:43,515
You have a package.

111
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:57,396
Here's your package.

112
00:07:59,464 --> 00:08:00,299
Thanks.

113
00:08:15,781 --> 00:08:16,615
What?

114
00:08:20,786 --> 00:08:21,620
No way.

115
00:08:23,522 --> 00:08:24,356
This...

116
00:08:26,225 --> 00:08:27,092
Dad.

117
00:08:27,693 --> 00:08:28,894
You'll get hurt, careful.

118
00:08:29,761 --> 00:08:32,364
Dad, I wanted this so badly.

119
00:08:32,364 --> 00:08:33,532
Do you think your dad
or mom wouldn't know...

120
00:08:33,532 --> 00:08:35,834
what you want?

121
00:08:35,834 --> 00:08:38,670
I'm going to draw so well with this.

122
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:39,738
All right.

123
00:08:39,738 --> 00:08:42,207
- My pretty girl.
- I love it.

124
00:08:58,190 --> 00:09:01,360
(Cheongham Flower Farm)

125
00:09:03,929 --> 00:09:04,763
There.

126
00:09:05,631 --> 00:09:06,465
Mom.

127
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,234
That's pretty.

128
00:09:09,801 --> 00:09:10,903
Three flowers?

129
00:09:11,403 --> 00:09:12,504
Is that our family?

130
00:09:12,504 --> 00:09:13,338
Yes.

131
00:09:14,940 --> 00:09:17,743
Who did you get those crafty hands from?

132
00:09:20,612 --> 00:09:21,446
Myo Jin.

133
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,016
- I'm going fishing.
- What?

134
00:09:24,650 --> 00:09:25,817
Wait for me!

135
00:09:27,186 --> 00:09:29,154
Hey, you'll fall.

136
00:09:29,154 --> 00:09:30,389
Be careful.

137
00:09:35,394 --> 00:09:36,628
Goodness.

138
00:10:35,621 --> 00:10:37,623
I never imagined...

139
00:10:39,658 --> 00:10:41,059
this was how you and I would end.

140
00:10:41,059 --> 00:10:41,994
Shut up.

141
00:10:43,795 --> 00:10:45,364
Even if you went back a hundred times,

142
00:10:46,331 --> 00:10:49,001
you'd do the same thing.
That's who you are.

143
00:15:01,453 --> 00:15:02,454
Please.

144
00:15:03,222 --> 00:15:04,823
Please!

145
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:13,365
Even after your memories came back,

146
00:15:14,233 --> 00:15:16,201
even after you learned everything,

147
00:15:17,903 --> 00:15:18,804
please,

148
00:15:19,471 --> 00:15:21,039
if you had just pretended not to know,

149
00:15:24,142 --> 00:15:25,978
we could've been happy.

150
00:15:26,278 --> 00:15:27,713
Shut up, you evil bastard.

151
00:15:36,822 --> 00:15:38,390
Over one stupid memory?

152
00:15:39,358 --> 00:15:41,660
It's already over and gone.

153
00:15:43,762 --> 00:15:46,031
You're the one trapped in old memories.

154
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:50,402
You're the one who can't get out.

155
00:15:53,705 --> 00:15:54,640
I'll kill you.

156
00:15:55,874 --> 00:15:56,675
Yes.

157
00:15:57,843 --> 00:15:58,744
Yes.

158
00:16:01,180 --> 00:16:02,915
I wish that too.

159
00:16:05,651 --> 00:16:06,585
I wish...

160
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:12,191
someone...

161
00:16:13,859 --> 00:16:15,027
would stop me.

162
00:16:22,501 --> 00:16:23,402
Yes.

163
00:16:25,838 --> 00:16:27,105
Let's go together.

164
00:16:32,044 --> 00:16:33,178
Ryu Jun Ho, stop.

165
00:16:33,178 --> 00:16:34,046
Now.

166
00:16:37,683 --> 00:16:38,617
Let go of her.

167
00:16:49,628 --> 00:16:50,562
Damn it.

168
00:17:02,007 --> 00:17:03,141
Ms. Ham.

169
00:17:03,141 --> 00:17:04,476
Ms. Ham, wake up.

170
00:17:12,518 --> 00:17:13,485
Please wake up.

171
00:17:18,657 --> 00:17:20,125
I'm home.

172
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:22,661
Honey, how was school?

173
00:17:22,661 --> 00:17:24,930
I bought snacks.

174
00:17:24,930 --> 00:17:25,731
Wait.

175
00:17:26,498 --> 00:17:27,499
Dad, what happened to your arm?

176
00:17:27,499 --> 00:17:30,369
This, well...

177
00:17:30,369 --> 00:17:31,436
- Right.
- Yeah?

178
00:17:31,837 --> 00:17:34,273
Did you tell your art club friends
to come over?

179
00:17:34,773 --> 00:17:37,509
I'll buy something tasty,
so bring everyone.

180
00:17:37,509 --> 00:17:40,112
You can all draw on that computer
and have fun.

181
00:17:41,213 --> 00:17:42,681
No, it's embarrassing.

182
00:17:43,649 --> 00:17:44,850
Embarrassing?

183
00:17:46,685 --> 00:17:48,320
I'm the only one without my own room.

184
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:49,688
I don't want to invite my friends.

185
00:17:50,589 --> 00:17:51,857
I see.

186
00:17:54,259 --> 00:17:56,361
But Dad, how did you hurt your arm?

187
00:17:57,362 --> 00:17:58,430
This?

188
00:17:59,698 --> 00:18:02,434
Earlier,

189
00:18:02,434 --> 00:18:04,403
- I was working in the field and...
- Yeah?

190
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:17,850
When the kids see our place,
they'll think it's kind of shabby, right?

191
00:18:17,850 --> 00:18:21,386
I told you not to keep telling her
to bring friends over.

192
00:18:21,386 --> 00:18:22,788
You're so clueless.

193
00:18:26,058 --> 00:18:26,925
Well,

194
00:18:29,495 --> 00:18:31,063
Myo Jin does need...

195
00:18:32,331 --> 00:18:34,199
her own room now.

196
00:18:36,502 --> 00:18:38,237
Of course, she does.

197
00:18:40,105 --> 00:18:43,342
Our daughter is a grown young lady now.

198
00:18:46,678 --> 00:18:47,746
With our situation,

199
00:18:49,681 --> 00:18:53,118
when could we ever find a place
with a proper room?

200
00:18:56,555 --> 00:18:58,123
Just wait and see.

201
00:18:58,123 --> 00:18:59,057
This time,

202
00:18:59,992 --> 00:19:02,628
who knows if we might get picked
for public housing?

203
00:19:04,763 --> 00:19:06,632
If we didn't get it last year,

204
00:19:07,599 --> 00:19:09,101
why would we get it this year?

205
00:19:10,903 --> 00:19:13,005
You and your bad luck.

206
00:19:14,239 --> 00:19:16,775
We need to give Myo Jin her own room.

207
00:19:20,279 --> 00:19:21,280
Still,

208
00:19:21,847 --> 00:19:24,483
Myo Jin is so bright.

209
00:19:27,719 --> 00:19:29,488
That puts my mind at ease.

210
00:19:29,855 --> 00:19:31,023
Goodness.

211
00:19:32,024 --> 00:19:33,826
Do you think she isn't hurting inside?

212
00:19:36,128 --> 00:19:37,763
She just doesn't say it.

213
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:42,501
Do you think I don't know...

214
00:19:45,003 --> 00:19:46,872
how deep-hearted Myo Jin is?

215
00:19:51,543 --> 00:19:54,079
You have to leave for work at dawn.
Go to sleep.

216
00:20:38,624 --> 00:20:39,992
I don't need anything else.

217
00:20:41,093 --> 00:20:42,227
Just tell me this.

218
00:20:43,795 --> 00:20:45,731
Did you kill my mom and dad?

219
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:49,334
Myo Jin!

220
00:20:51,703 --> 00:20:53,138
Do you miss your parents?

221
00:20:54,373 --> 00:20:56,275
Will you only be satisfied
after seeing blood?

222
00:20:56,742 --> 00:20:58,143
If you want revenge,

223
00:20:58,577 --> 00:21:00,579
get your head on straight first.

224
00:21:01,013 --> 00:21:02,981
Do whatever it takes
to recover your memories.

225
00:21:03,649 --> 00:21:05,350
The things I told you.

226
00:21:05,951 --> 00:21:07,819
No matter how bad the accident was,

227
00:21:08,420 --> 00:21:09,288
they're not something...

228
00:21:09,988 --> 00:21:11,957
you can just forget.

229
00:21:11,957 --> 00:21:13,525
I tried hundreds of times,

230
00:21:13,926 --> 00:21:15,394
but nothing worked.

231
00:21:16,929 --> 00:21:19,331
Coming to you was
the last thing I could do.

232
00:21:19,331 --> 00:21:21,466
It isn't true that I confessed
to the police...

233
00:21:21,466 --> 00:21:23,468
I set the fire by mistake.

234
00:21:24,570 --> 00:21:26,805
The truth I hid
even when I went to prison...

235
00:21:27,506 --> 00:21:30,309
and told only you.

236
00:21:31,076 --> 00:21:32,845
You still don't remember it?

237
00:21:34,146 --> 00:21:35,147
None of it?

238
00:21:36,415 --> 00:21:37,349
Tell me...

239
00:21:38,517 --> 00:21:39,751
what happened.

240
00:21:42,087 --> 00:21:44,423
Who killed my mom and dad, and why?

241
00:21:57,936 --> 00:22:01,006
This cancer is eating my body away.

242
00:22:12,551 --> 00:22:14,453
I don't know what'll happen or when.

243
00:22:15,487 --> 00:22:16,555
So I kept something.

244
00:22:26,798 --> 00:22:28,534
I told you...

245
00:22:30,502 --> 00:22:32,804
the first time you came
saying you'd kill me.

246
00:22:33,438 --> 00:22:34,540
A guy like me...

247
00:22:35,774 --> 00:22:37,242
doesn't trust the world.

248
00:22:39,478 --> 00:22:41,613
What you can trust isn't people or money.

249
00:22:43,715 --> 00:22:45,817
It's the insurance you keep on them.

250
00:22:47,085 --> 00:22:48,086
Lee Jong Su.

251
00:22:49,488 --> 00:22:51,924
He's the guy who brought
Chairman Choi Young Ho's money.

252
00:22:53,192 --> 00:22:55,194
I recorded my conversation with him.

253
00:22:55,727 --> 00:22:57,262
There will come a time when you need it.

254
00:22:57,896 --> 00:22:58,964
Then this is...

255
00:22:59,932 --> 00:23:00,866
Listen to it.

256
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:04,303
You won't have anything left
to wonder about.

257
00:23:08,740 --> 00:23:09,675
Now go.

258
00:23:11,276 --> 00:23:12,845
And don't ever come back.

259
00:23:18,383 --> 00:23:19,751
I won't be here even if you do.

260
00:24:08,867 --> 00:24:09,768
Seriously?

261
00:24:10,569 --> 00:24:14,106
They make me do
all kinds of ridiculous crap.

262
00:24:17,075 --> 00:24:18,010
This is it.

263
00:24:30,589 --> 00:24:32,691
Are you on your way back
from the hospital?

264
00:24:34,827 --> 00:24:36,628
I cleaned this morning.

265
00:24:36,628 --> 00:24:38,630
I just did this
while I was cleaning the second floor.

266
00:24:38,630 --> 00:24:40,232
By the way, what did the hospital say?

267
00:24:41,333 --> 00:24:43,535
They said I'm recovering
faster than expected...

268
00:24:43,535 --> 00:24:45,437
and told me to take
even better care of myself.

269
00:24:45,437 --> 00:24:47,639
See? What did I tell you?

270
00:24:47,639 --> 00:24:49,942
If you do what I say,
you'll get better in no time.

271
00:24:50,442 --> 00:24:51,343
I'm happy for you.

272
00:25:12,130 --> 00:25:15,000
(Atibam)

273
00:25:47,432 --> 00:25:48,700
Good morning.

274
00:25:52,571 --> 00:25:54,806
Is there any place in particular
that feels uncomfortable?

275
00:25:55,908 --> 00:25:57,242
No, I'm fine.

276
00:25:58,377 --> 00:26:01,180
Your test results are all normal.

277
00:26:01,547 --> 00:26:02,447
That's a relief.

278
00:26:02,915 --> 00:26:05,083
The anesthetic that paralyzed your body...

279
00:26:05,083 --> 00:26:06,885
has been completely cleared.

280
00:26:07,186 --> 00:26:09,221
You're healthy enough...

281
00:26:09,221 --> 00:26:10,189
to be discharged today.

282
00:26:11,056 --> 00:26:12,090
Thank you.

283
00:26:15,093 --> 00:26:15,994
Doctor.

284
00:26:17,896 --> 00:26:20,465
Can I ask what happened to Ryu Jun Ho?

285
00:26:22,768 --> 00:26:25,370
You mean the suspect
with the gunshot wound?

286
00:26:26,538 --> 00:26:27,372
Yes.

287
00:26:27,940 --> 00:26:31,009
I heard his injuries are serious,
so he's in the ICU.

288
00:26:33,312 --> 00:26:34,980
If he's in the ICU,

289
00:26:36,048 --> 00:26:37,983
does that mean his life isn't in danger?

290
00:26:38,317 --> 00:26:39,651
Yes, that's right.

291
00:26:40,419 --> 00:26:42,321
Even if someone is a major criminal,

292
00:26:42,321 --> 00:26:43,755
in cases like this,

293
00:26:43,755 --> 00:26:44,857
for the sake of the investigation,

294
00:26:44,857 --> 00:26:46,892
they usually do everything they can
to keep them alive.

295
00:26:48,026 --> 00:26:49,328
Is he in this hospital?

296
00:26:50,229 --> 00:26:51,096
No.

297
00:26:51,463 --> 00:26:52,664
Since he's a murder suspect,

298
00:26:52,664 --> 00:26:54,433
he's under separate protection.

299
00:26:55,133 --> 00:26:57,336
He's under special police supervision,

300
00:26:57,336 --> 00:26:59,805
so even we don't know where he is.

301
00:27:00,639 --> 00:27:02,007
I see.

302
00:27:03,642 --> 00:27:04,409
Take care.

303
00:27:14,586 --> 00:27:18,790
(Seoul Namyeong Police Station)

304
00:27:19,091 --> 00:27:20,459
It seems Ryu Jun Ho...

305
00:27:20,459 --> 00:27:23,495
planned to make it look as though you,

306
00:27:23,495 --> 00:27:25,764
after killing Choi Young Ho
and Choi Hee Su to avenge your parents,

307
00:27:26,665 --> 00:27:29,334
also killed Wang Gi Cheol,

308
00:27:29,334 --> 00:27:31,103
who was paid to give
false testimony for them,

309
00:27:31,103 --> 00:27:34,072
and then staged everything
as an impulsive suicide...

310
00:27:34,072 --> 00:27:36,642
caused by traumatic brain injury.

311
00:27:37,342 --> 00:27:40,445
Even though he knew you were recovering,

312
00:27:40,946 --> 00:27:43,282
he kept making you take
medication for schizophrenia,

313
00:27:43,649 --> 00:27:45,717
deleted the recordings...

314
00:27:45,717 --> 00:27:48,053
that could have exposed his past actions,

315
00:27:48,453 --> 00:27:49,822
and they were all part
of the same pattern.

316
00:27:52,958 --> 00:27:54,393
On the day of the incident,

317
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:56,461
the secretary, Director Kim Won Il,

318
00:27:56,895 --> 00:27:59,665
used a forged passport
and attended the conference in Germany...

319
00:27:59,665 --> 00:28:01,733
in Ryu Jun Ho's place.

320
00:28:02,134 --> 00:28:04,336
But when we actually began
tracing his accounts,

321
00:28:04,803 --> 00:28:06,171
he confessed to everything.

322
00:28:09,141 --> 00:28:10,609
How are you feeling, Ms. Ham?

323
00:28:13,745 --> 00:28:16,048
Thanks to you, I'm much better, Detective.

324
00:28:16,048 --> 00:28:17,549
I don't have to go
to the hospital anymore, either.

325
00:28:18,584 --> 00:28:19,751
That's really good to hear.

326
00:28:20,352 --> 00:28:22,921
What happens from here?

327
00:28:24,156 --> 00:28:25,290
In about two weeks,

328
00:28:25,290 --> 00:28:27,793
the full investigation will begin.

329
00:28:27,793 --> 00:28:30,295
In the end,
it'll become a battle over sentencing.

330
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:32,931
I see.

331
00:28:33,532 --> 00:28:36,134
Ryu Jun Ho is currently
exercising his right to remain silent,

332
00:28:36,134 --> 00:28:38,704
so we still haven't heard directly...

333
00:28:38,704 --> 00:28:40,706
why he tried to kill you, Ms. Ham.

334
00:28:41,974 --> 00:28:42,875
Detective.

335
00:28:44,142 --> 00:28:46,144
If Ryu Jun Ho is staying silent...

336
00:28:47,779 --> 00:28:49,381
What you're assuming is right.

337
00:28:49,882 --> 00:28:51,517
The country's top law firm
is representing him.

338
00:28:52,518 --> 00:28:54,319
He's rich,

339
00:28:54,319 --> 00:28:56,522
so he's put together
an extremely high-end defense team.

340
00:28:59,525 --> 00:29:00,626
Now,

341
00:29:00,626 --> 00:29:03,428
has your suspicion about Ms. Ham's
Jebu-do Island accident...

342
00:29:03,428 --> 00:29:04,963
been cleared up, Detective Woo?

343
00:29:04,963 --> 00:29:06,431
Of course.

344
00:29:07,065 --> 00:29:08,634
I've been very rude all this time.

345
00:29:11,637 --> 00:29:14,006
She went all the way to the villa
to save Choi Hee Su...

346
00:29:14,773 --> 00:29:16,308
and nearly lost her life.

347
00:29:16,909 --> 00:29:19,011
The shock of that moment
and the accident...

348
00:29:19,645 --> 00:29:21,847
are what have tormented Ms. Ham until now.

349
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,549
I'm glad the misunderstanding
has been cleared up.

350
00:29:25,284 --> 00:29:26,685
I have a favor to ask.

351
00:29:28,787 --> 00:29:31,023
Please let me see Ryu Jun Ho
one last time.

352
00:29:39,097 --> 00:29:40,732
I want to return it to him myself.

353
00:29:43,569 --> 00:29:45,270
Yes, of course.

354
00:29:46,138 --> 00:29:47,139
Thank you.

355
00:29:59,551 --> 00:30:00,652
Questioning as a witness?

356
00:30:00,652 --> 00:30:01,720
What bullshit.

357
00:30:02,421 --> 00:30:03,755
I wasn't born yesterday.

358
00:30:04,389 --> 00:30:06,792
It's all because of that idiot.

359
00:30:07,426 --> 00:30:09,528
I'll never work with
brainless bastards again.

360
00:30:10,062 --> 00:30:10,996
Damn it.

361
00:30:17,803 --> 00:30:19,304
I'm sorry! Are you hurt?

362
00:30:21,373 --> 00:30:22,241
No.

363
00:30:23,208 --> 00:30:24,209
Are you Korean?

364
00:30:24,810 --> 00:30:26,512
Do you speak Korean?

365
00:30:26,979 --> 00:30:28,947
Well, I'm an overseas Chinese.

366
00:30:29,348 --> 00:30:30,449
But are you okay?

367
00:30:30,449 --> 00:30:31,316
Are you hurt?

368
00:30:31,316 --> 00:30:32,184
I'm sorry.

369
00:30:32,551 --> 00:30:33,652
I'm okay.

370
00:30:35,153 --> 00:30:36,688
I missed my flight last week,

371
00:30:36,688 --> 00:30:38,724
so I was rushing a little today
and caused this accident.

372
00:30:41,593 --> 00:30:43,729
I wish there were
more flights to Hong Kong.

373
00:30:43,996 --> 00:30:44,930
Are you going to Hong Kong?

374
00:30:45,764 --> 00:30:47,099
Same as me.

375
00:30:47,099 --> 00:30:48,500
- Really?
- Yes.

376
00:30:48,901 --> 00:30:51,270
I go every week for work.

377
00:30:53,405 --> 00:30:54,506
But the time...

378
00:30:56,942 --> 00:30:58,744
Would you like to talk
while we go together?

379
00:30:59,077 --> 00:31:00,012
Sure.

380
00:31:01,213 --> 00:31:02,147
Let's go.

381
00:31:02,147 --> 00:31:03,015
Thanks.

382
00:31:35,981 --> 00:31:37,816
(Restricted Area)

383
00:31:44,656 --> 00:31:46,692
I did receive Detective Woo's call,

384
00:31:47,326 --> 00:31:48,393
but because of the patient's condition,

385
00:31:48,961 --> 00:31:50,462
I can't give you much time.

386
00:31:51,697 --> 00:31:52,798
Yes, I understand.

387
00:31:53,699 --> 00:31:55,267
When you're finished,

388
00:31:55,267 --> 00:31:56,502
press this button.

389
00:31:57,836 --> 00:31:59,771
Then a nurse will come and escort you out.

390
00:32:01,473 --> 00:32:04,176
Can he hear my voice?

391
00:32:05,043 --> 00:32:05,811
Yes.

392
00:32:07,012 --> 00:32:07,846
Mr. Ryu.

393
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:09,815
Ms. Ham is here.

394
00:32:55,294 --> 00:32:56,762
I was afraid.

395
00:33:03,669 --> 00:33:06,171
If your memories came back,

396
00:33:08,373 --> 00:33:10,142
you'd learn everything,

397
00:33:14,146 --> 00:33:16,515
and you'd leave me.

398
00:33:21,286 --> 00:33:22,588
Then I'd go back...

399
00:33:24,723 --> 00:33:26,658
to the past again.

400
00:33:43,108 --> 00:33:44,376
For one brief moment,

401
00:33:48,614 --> 00:33:49,615
there was a time...

402
00:33:51,250 --> 00:33:53,418
when I doubted you.

403
00:34:09,434 --> 00:34:10,836
(Voice Mail)

404
00:34:10,836 --> 00:34:12,337
(You have a new voice message.)

405
00:34:14,373 --> 00:34:15,307
Jun Ho.

406
00:34:15,807 --> 00:34:18,076
Your phone is off,
so I'll leave a voice message.

407
00:34:19,311 --> 00:34:20,379
Tonight,

408
00:34:21,213 --> 00:34:22,881
I don't think I can meet you.

409
00:34:29,588 --> 00:34:31,390
I should have stopped then.

410
00:34:37,029 --> 00:34:38,831
It was the last chance...

411
00:34:41,934 --> 00:34:43,202
to get away from you,

412
00:34:46,872 --> 00:34:48,307
but I threw it away.

413
00:34:51,510 --> 00:34:52,377
That's right.

414
00:34:58,317 --> 00:35:00,185
Every choice was yours.

415
00:35:05,390 --> 00:35:08,126
You must have hoped
my memories would never return.

416
00:35:10,229 --> 00:35:11,497
Because you wanted me
to forget everything...

417
00:35:12,998 --> 00:35:15,868
and live inside the cage you built for us.

418
00:35:16,768 --> 00:35:19,404
(Change of Address Form, Ham Myo Jin)

419
00:35:22,808 --> 00:35:24,209
Here you go.

420
00:35:24,510 --> 00:35:25,878
Yes, that's all set.

421
00:35:30,582 --> 00:35:31,550
This is him.

422
00:35:33,185 --> 00:35:33,986
Okay.

423
00:35:50,636 --> 00:35:51,470
What?

424
00:35:56,175 --> 00:35:58,944
But my feelings remembered you,

425
00:36:00,746 --> 00:36:02,781
and they showed me what I had to do.

426
00:36:08,187 --> 00:36:09,955
I came to say thank you.

427
00:36:11,790 --> 00:36:13,892
After the accident,
if it hadn't been for you,

428
00:36:15,994 --> 00:36:18,063
none of this would have been possible.

429
00:36:30,876 --> 00:36:32,211
The police said...

430
00:36:35,514 --> 00:36:37,516
I killed...

431
00:36:41,453 --> 00:36:42,387
Hee Su.

432
00:36:43,021 --> 00:36:45,324
What do they mean, I killed her?

433
00:36:46,859 --> 00:36:47,693
That day,

434
00:36:52,898 --> 00:36:56,702
I did try to kill those two,

435
00:36:58,971 --> 00:37:00,038
but I didn't...

436
00:37:03,742 --> 00:37:04,643
think of...

437
00:37:05,410 --> 00:37:06,411
doing so brutally.

438
00:37:08,180 --> 00:37:09,348
At least,

439
00:37:13,085 --> 00:37:14,186
I never...

440
00:37:17,356 --> 00:37:19,124
thought of doing it that way.

441
00:37:32,070 --> 00:37:32,938
Was it...

442
00:37:38,110 --> 00:37:39,411
you?

443
00:37:41,180 --> 00:37:42,314
Don't be curious.

444
00:37:44,249 --> 00:37:46,518
It's meaningless to you now anyway.

445
00:37:47,286 --> 00:37:48,253
Were...

446
00:37:52,191 --> 00:37:54,393
all the moments you spent with me...

447
00:37:56,161 --> 00:37:56,995
really...

448
00:38:01,300 --> 00:38:04,036
all lies?

449
00:38:06,071 --> 00:38:08,040
I'm surprised...

450
00:38:08,941 --> 00:38:09,975
you still wonder that.

451
00:38:17,850 --> 00:38:18,917
Why...

452
00:38:22,654 --> 00:38:24,623
be that cruel?

453
00:38:26,225 --> 00:38:27,092
Because that day,

454
00:38:29,895 --> 00:38:32,431
you were the one who set fire to my house.

455
00:38:34,700 --> 00:38:35,634
Because you...

456
00:38:36,502 --> 00:38:38,971
are the murderer
who killed my mom and dad.

457
00:38:56,288 --> 00:38:58,090
You'd better brace yourself.

458
00:39:07,032 --> 00:39:09,468
Until your whole body rots away,

459
00:39:10,802 --> 00:39:12,070
slowly, step by step,

460
00:39:13,539 --> 00:39:15,040
I'm going to break you down.

461
00:39:17,910 --> 00:39:18,944
Please...

462
00:39:21,980 --> 00:39:23,048
die slowly.

463
00:39:45,204 --> 00:39:47,472
(No Unauthorized Entry)

464
00:41:29,074 --> 00:41:30,642
(The late Ham Jun Seong, Lee Yoo Jeong,
2010.03.16)

465
00:41:30,642 --> 00:41:31,810
(Mom, Dad, rest in peace.)

466
00:41:32,244 --> 00:41:33,245
Dad.

467
00:41:35,714 --> 00:41:36,615
Mom.

468
00:41:39,218 --> 00:41:40,252
I'm here.

469
00:41:42,287 --> 00:41:43,555
I'm sorry...

470
00:41:46,892 --> 00:41:47,826
I came so late.

471
00:42:11,049 --> 00:42:12,084
Welcome.

472
00:42:14,686 --> 00:42:15,854
It's been a while.

473
00:42:21,493 --> 00:42:23,595
One pour-over coffee, please.

474
00:42:25,597 --> 00:42:26,765
It's all right.

475
00:42:27,266 --> 00:42:29,868
I'm curious to taste the coffee
you make yourself, Ms. Ham.

476
00:43:11,877 --> 00:43:12,845
It's good.

477
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:16,315
It feels perfect.

478
00:43:24,056 --> 00:43:25,090
Last week,

479
00:43:25,724 --> 00:43:27,893
the police came
as part of the investigation.

480
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:30,762
I heard about your parents, Ms. Ham,

481
00:43:31,430 --> 00:43:33,432
and looked up the articles
from back then too.

482
00:43:34,500 --> 00:43:37,870
The reactions you showed
during the initial tests...

483
00:43:38,337 --> 00:43:40,906
seemed like unrelated answers every time,

484
00:43:41,607 --> 00:43:44,176
but when I analyzed them again,
that wasn't the case.

485
00:43:50,883 --> 00:43:52,784
A thought suddenly occurred to me.

486
00:43:54,152 --> 00:43:55,787
Maybe everyone, myself included,

487
00:43:55,787 --> 00:43:57,956
was completely fooled.

488
00:43:58,490 --> 00:44:00,425
Choi Hee Su, Ryu Jun Ho,

489
00:44:00,425 --> 00:44:02,761
Chairman Choi Young Ho and Wang Gi Cheol.

490
00:44:03,362 --> 00:44:06,865
Everyone who brought tragedy
to your family is dead,

491
00:44:07,866 --> 00:44:09,201
and that can't be a coincidence.

492
00:44:13,972 --> 00:44:16,108
Is that how I look to you, Doctor?

493
00:44:16,808 --> 00:44:18,677
I didn't come here with any other reason.

494
00:44:19,344 --> 00:44:20,546
As a doctor,

495
00:44:20,546 --> 00:44:22,681
I was left with one unanswered question.

496
00:44:25,584 --> 00:44:26,852
When did it start?

497
00:44:27,819 --> 00:44:30,122
When did you begin hiding
that your memories had returned?

498
00:44:31,456 --> 00:44:33,225
Even if I told you,

499
00:44:33,992 --> 00:44:35,427
it wouldn't matter anymore.

500
00:44:36,662 --> 00:44:37,529
Why not?

501
00:44:40,098 --> 00:44:41,366
Because memories...

502
00:44:42,201 --> 00:44:43,435
belong to the past,

503
00:44:46,972 --> 00:44:48,941
and the past can't be undone.

504
00:44:51,176 --> 00:44:52,344
I told you.

505
00:44:52,578 --> 00:44:55,247
Back then, we got acceptance letters
from the best universities in America.

506
00:44:55,247 --> 00:44:56,114
Can that...

507
00:44:58,016 --> 00:45:00,185
be a reason to kill people?

508
00:45:05,157 --> 00:45:07,059
People with nothing to lose...

509
00:45:07,926 --> 00:45:10,429
all think like you, of course.

510
00:45:11,830 --> 00:45:12,664
What?

511
00:45:14,766 --> 00:45:15,601
You.

512
00:45:16,134 --> 00:45:18,370
When you first came to my exhibition
and saw my paintings, you cried.

513
00:45:19,304 --> 00:45:20,372
You said it yourself...

514
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:23,041
that you could feel
my sorrow inside my paintings.

515
00:45:23,408 --> 00:45:24,343
My passion,

516
00:45:24,977 --> 00:45:27,179
my talent, all of it, so vividly.

517
00:45:27,813 --> 00:45:29,748
You said that you'd never felt
anything like it before.

518
00:45:31,250 --> 00:45:32,417
You're insane.

519
00:45:33,785 --> 00:45:36,121
If those people had ruined me back then,

520
00:45:42,427 --> 00:45:43,495
my paintings...

521
00:45:45,764 --> 00:45:47,332
wouldn't exist in the world now.

522
00:45:51,403 --> 00:45:52,771
Can you even imagine that?

523
00:46:03,448 --> 00:46:04,349
Hey.

524
00:46:04,616 --> 00:46:07,319
Do you know
what people with nothing to lose...

525
00:46:08,887 --> 00:46:10,689
are capable of?

526
00:46:14,860 --> 00:46:15,994
They just wait for their chance.

527
00:46:16,862 --> 00:46:19,464
They wait to find fault
with people who have money,

528
00:46:19,832 --> 00:46:21,733
and when they get the chance,
they pounce and rip them apart.

529
00:46:21,733 --> 00:46:22,568
Like animals.

530
00:46:23,569 --> 00:46:25,370
That's what happened to us that day.

531
00:46:26,271 --> 00:46:28,407
There is no one in this world
who has nothing to lose.

532
00:46:29,341 --> 00:46:31,743
Because those people were
someone's father and someone's mother too.

533
00:46:31,743 --> 00:46:33,512
Stop with the pathetic sob story.

534
00:46:35,380 --> 00:46:37,349
Who do you think you are
to talk to me like that?

535
00:46:37,349 --> 00:46:38,750
Are you saying I should've been ruined...

536
00:46:38,750 --> 00:46:40,886
because of people like them?

537
00:46:41,320 --> 00:46:42,120
I...

538
00:46:42,521 --> 00:46:44,323
am not like those people.

539
00:46:45,023 --> 00:46:47,459
I'm not one of those beastly types
who swarm like dogs...

540
00:46:47,459 --> 00:46:49,695
at the slightest opening
just to squeeze money out of people.

541
00:47:39,511 --> 00:47:40,345
This is insane.

542
00:47:41,547 --> 00:47:42,614
They're all insane.

543
00:48:09,208 --> 00:48:11,243
Why is it so noisy?

544
00:48:33,198 --> 00:48:34,032
Hee Su.

545
00:48:34,366 --> 00:48:35,267
Hee Su.

546
00:49:35,961 --> 00:49:37,963
Suspected traffic accident patient.

547
00:49:37,963 --> 00:49:40,132
Blood pressure 90 over 60.

548
00:49:40,432 --> 00:49:41,767
Ryu Jun Ho...

549
00:49:41,767 --> 00:49:43,502
Suspected thoracoabdominal trauma
and femur fracture.

550
00:49:43,502 --> 00:49:46,471
- killed...
- Requesting trauma team standby.

551
00:49:46,872 --> 00:49:49,842
- my mom and dad.
- Copy. The trauma team will stand by.

552
00:49:49,842 --> 00:49:50,943
I mustn't...

553
00:49:51,910 --> 00:49:53,512
- forget.
- Patient is being transported.

554
00:49:53,512 --> 00:49:55,013
The patient is unresponsive.

555
00:49:55,013 --> 00:49:56,348
That man...

556
00:49:58,617 --> 00:49:59,618
killed...

557
00:50:00,719 --> 00:50:02,087
my mom and...

558
00:50:02,087 --> 00:50:03,455
Check the bleeding sites again.

559
00:50:04,590 --> 00:50:06,959
(Rescue Team)

560
00:50:12,498 --> 00:50:13,332
Emergency patient.

561
00:50:13,332 --> 00:50:15,067
She was conscious at the scene,

562
00:50:15,067 --> 00:50:16,802
but lost consciousness again
during transport.

563
00:50:16,802 --> 00:50:18,270
Move her to the OR quickly.

564
00:50:18,270 --> 00:50:19,838
- Call a surgeon.
- Yes.

565
00:50:19,838 --> 00:50:20,973
(Central Surgery Center)

566
00:50:28,914 --> 00:50:29,781
Ma'am.

567
00:50:30,015 --> 00:50:31,116
Can you hear me?

568
00:50:31,416 --> 00:50:32,584
Can you hear me?

569
00:50:40,492 --> 00:50:41,260
Yes?

570
00:50:43,162 --> 00:50:44,096
What did you say?

571
00:50:44,997 --> 00:50:45,998
When I wake up,

572
00:50:46,798 --> 00:50:48,066
tell me...

573
00:50:52,271 --> 00:50:53,372
that Ryu Jun Ho...

574
00:50:55,374 --> 00:50:57,042
killed...

575
00:50:58,610 --> 00:50:59,711
my mom and dad.

576
00:51:02,915 --> 00:51:05,517
I must never forget.

577
00:51:10,389 --> 00:51:11,223
I must...

578
00:51:12,858 --> 00:51:14,726
remember.

579
00:51:16,962 --> 00:51:17,830
Ryu...

580
00:51:18,297 --> 00:51:19,264
Jun...

581
00:51:20,465 --> 00:51:21,400
Ho...

582
00:51:42,287 --> 00:51:43,222
Myo Jin.

583
00:51:43,555 --> 00:51:44,823
Please wake up.

584
00:51:48,427 --> 00:51:49,461
Are you coming around?

585
00:51:52,097 --> 00:51:53,966
Jun Ho.

586
00:51:55,334 --> 00:51:56,168
What?

587
00:51:57,302 --> 00:51:58,337
Ryu...

588
00:52:00,672 --> 00:52:01,974
Jun Ho.

589
00:52:02,708 --> 00:52:03,675
Yes, that's right.

590
00:52:05,477 --> 00:52:06,378
It's me.

591
00:52:07,179 --> 00:52:08,480
Ryu Jun Ho.

592
00:52:16,822 --> 00:52:17,756
Myo Jin.

593
00:52:32,571 --> 00:52:33,472
I...

594
00:52:35,140 --> 00:52:36,175
told you, didn't I?

595
00:52:38,410 --> 00:52:39,444
When you...

596
00:52:40,979 --> 00:52:42,948
first woke up after the accident,

597
00:52:46,785 --> 00:52:48,020
you didn't remember your own name,

598
00:52:50,255 --> 00:52:51,390
your family's names,

599
00:52:55,060 --> 00:52:56,195
or anything at all.

600
00:52:57,162 --> 00:52:58,897
Nothing at all.

601
00:53:01,266 --> 00:53:03,101
But...

602
00:53:05,404 --> 00:53:06,672
you only remembered...

603
00:53:08,907 --> 00:53:10,242
my name.

604
00:53:44,710 --> 00:53:46,445
You can forget everything else.

605
00:53:48,881 --> 00:53:49,781
Just keep...

606
00:53:51,250 --> 00:53:52,284
remembering...

607
00:53:56,588 --> 00:53:57,489
only me,

608
00:53:58,724 --> 00:54:00,159
like you do now.

609
00:54:06,064 --> 00:54:07,032
Forever.

610
00:54:25,751 --> 00:54:27,653
Have you ever felt truly terrified?

611
00:54:30,756 --> 00:54:33,292
That fear that everything
could collapse in an instant,

612
00:54:36,328 --> 00:54:39,965
and someone might make
your life turn out that way.

613
00:54:42,134 --> 00:54:45,304
You have a capable father
and someone you love.

614
00:54:46,805 --> 00:54:47,906
What are you afraid of?

615
00:54:52,411 --> 00:54:56,248
Everyone has at least one secret
they can't tell anyone.

616
00:54:59,117 --> 00:54:59,952
Mine...

617
00:55:00,986 --> 00:55:03,522
came too early.

618
00:55:05,424 --> 00:55:06,291
A secret?

619
00:55:07,125 --> 00:55:07,960
Yes.

620
00:55:08,527 --> 00:55:09,394
A secret...

621
00:55:12,231 --> 00:55:15,033
preserved like a specimen
until the day I die,

622
00:55:16,134 --> 00:55:17,503
following me everywhere.

623
00:55:22,107 --> 00:55:23,809
What kind of secret stays hidden forever?

624
00:55:30,682 --> 00:55:31,583
Is that so?

625
00:55:35,354 --> 00:55:38,490
Someone might already know it.

626
00:55:44,263 --> 00:55:45,397
You have...

627
00:55:47,166 --> 00:55:48,033
a secret too.

628
00:55:49,234 --> 00:55:50,068
What?

629
00:55:53,705 --> 00:55:54,573
I,

630
00:55:56,942 --> 00:55:58,010
sometimes,

631
00:55:59,611 --> 00:56:02,047
want to let everything go.

632
00:56:05,751 --> 00:56:07,286
I'm so tired.

633
00:56:12,291 --> 00:56:13,425
It's too hard.

634
00:56:19,298 --> 00:56:20,199
Myo Jin.

635
00:56:22,034 --> 00:56:23,902
Have you ever received a present?

636
00:56:46,124 --> 00:56:46,959
Myo Jin.

637
00:56:47,659 --> 00:56:49,695
Please put that away for me.

638
00:56:51,296 --> 00:56:52,698
That's...

639
00:56:52,698 --> 00:56:55,467
because the chairman and Ms. Choi
have this condition.

640
00:56:56,134 --> 00:56:58,270
They can't look at anything sharp.

641
00:57:01,974 --> 00:57:02,875
A present?

642
00:57:03,642 --> 00:57:05,010
Yes, a present.

643
00:57:08,747 --> 00:57:09,615
I don't know.

644
00:57:10,616 --> 00:57:13,352
I've never lived thinking
about things like that.

645
00:57:20,726 --> 00:57:21,894
Then should I give...

646
00:57:23,095 --> 00:57:23,996
that present to you?

647
00:57:24,730 --> 00:57:25,731
You? To me?

648
00:57:26,598 --> 00:57:27,432
Why?

649
00:57:29,034 --> 00:57:29,902
Just...

650
00:57:34,573 --> 00:57:36,608
because when I look at you sometimes,

651
00:57:39,578 --> 00:57:41,480
you feel similar to me.

652
00:57:53,292 --> 00:57:55,427
There is no one in this world
who has nothing to lose.

653
00:57:56,395 --> 00:57:58,764
Because those people were
someone's father and someone's mother too.

654
00:57:58,764 --> 00:58:00,532
Stop with the pathetic sob story.

655
00:58:02,434 --> 00:58:04,469
Who do you think you are
to talk to me like that?

656
00:58:04,469 --> 00:58:05,704
Are you saying I should've been ruined...

657
00:58:05,704 --> 00:58:07,940
because of people like them?

658
00:58:08,340 --> 00:58:09,141
I...

659
00:58:09,508 --> 00:58:11,276
am not like those people.

660
00:58:12,077 --> 00:58:14,479
I'm not one of those beastly types
who swarm like dogs...

661
00:58:14,479 --> 00:58:16,715
at the slightest opening
just to squeeze money out of people.

662
00:59:45,003 --> 00:59:47,005
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

663
00:59:47,940 --> 00:59:52,678
(REVERSE)
